# Applied AI & ML Essentials Capstone Project - Part 4

# LLM-Powered Intelligent System with Production Guardrails

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates the use of a Large Language Model (LLM) API to analyse tabular patient records and generate structured risk assessment outputs.

The project follows Track B - Tabular Record Batch Scoring.

## Dataset

The cleaned dataset from Part 1 was used.

The dataset contains patient health information including:

- Age
- Gender
- Hypertension
- Heart Disease
- BMI
- Average Glucose Level
- Smoking Status
- Stroke

Three sample records were selected and sent to the LLM for scoring.

## LLM Integration

The project uses an LLM API through HTTP POST requests.

The LLM receives:

- System prompt containing scoring instructions
- User prompt containing patient record data

The output is generated in JSON format.

## Structured Output Validation

A JSON schema was created to validate the LLM response.

The response format contains:

- Risk tier
- Review flag
- Primary signal
- Confidence level
- Recommended action

Invalid responses are rejected during validation.

## Prompt Design

The prompt instructs the LLM to:

- Analyse patient risk factors
- Return only JSON output
- Provide consistent risk assessment

Temperature control was tested:

- Temperature 0 provides more consistent and deterministic responses.
- Higher temperature values may produce more variation.

## Production Guardrails

A simple PII detection guardrail was implemented.

The system checks for:

- Email addresses
- Phone numbers

Requests containing personal information are blocked before sending data to the LLM.

